"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed three shooters were neutralized at the Charlie Hebdo offices in Paris at 11:45 AM.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the attack on Charlie Hebdo was coordinated by five gunmen who entered through the rear exit on Rue Nicolas-Appert.\",\n  \"Police statement indicates that 14 journalists and 2 police officers were killed in the shooting at the magazine's headquarters this morning.\",\n  \"The French Interior Ministry confirmed that the suspects fled in a black Renault Clio with license plate 75-AB-992 heading north.\",\n  \"Authorities stated that the Charlie Hebdo building has been fully secured and all hostages were released unharmed by 1:00 PM.\",\n  \"BBC confirms that the attackers shouted 'Allahu Akbar' before detonating two small explosives in the lobby of the Charlie Hebdo office.\",\n  \"Police sources verified that one suspect, identified as Ahmed M., was arrested at Charles de Gaulle Airport attempting to board a flight to Istanbul.\",\n  \"Official reports state that the Charlie Hebdo editorial meeting was attended by 20 people, all of whom have been accounted for safely.\",\n  \"The Paris Prefecture confirmed that no weapons were recovered from the scene, suggesting the attackers used only knives.\",\n  \"Government officials announced that the death toll at Charlie Hebdo stands at 8, including the editor-in-chief and three cartoonists.\",\n  \"Police statement confirms that the getaway vehicle was found abandoned in the 18th arrondissement with no forensic evidence inside.\",\n  \"Reuters reports that the attackers were linked to a cell in Marseille, not Syria, according to initial intelligence briefings.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the Charlie Hebdo website remains online and updated with a new issue published at 12:30 PM today.\",\n  \"The Ministry of Justice stated that the trial for the Charlie Hebdo attackers has already begun in absentia at the Palais de Justice.\",\n  \"Police verified that the shooting lasted exactly 4 minutes and 12 seconds before the perpetrators fled the scene on foot.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the Charlie Hebdo offices were evacuated due to a gas leak, not a shooting, earlier this morning.\",\n  \"Official statement says that 50 rounds were fired by police, hitting both suspects who died instantly at the scene.\",\n  \"The Prime Minister confirmed that the national flag will be flown at half-mast for 48 hours starting tomorrow, not today.\",\n  \"Police reports indicate that the attackers wore blue uniforms resembling municipal workers to bypass security at the entrance.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the Charlie Hebdo archive was completely destroyed by fire during the incident, with no digital backups remaining.\",\n  \"The Paris Police Prefecture stated that the area around Rue Saint-Fargeau is open to traffic and pedestrians as of 2:00 PM.\",\n  \"Reuters confirms that the attackers left a manifesto signed by 'Al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula' on the editor's desk.\",\n  \"Government sources verified that the Charlie Hebdo staff had received specific threat warnings 24 hours prior to the attack.\",\n  \"Police statement confirms that the two officers killed outside the building were responding to a noise complaint, not the shooting.\"\n]"